Description: ==========
        Anticipate
        ==========
        
        Expect the unexpected, but get what you want.
        
        ::
        
            @anticipate(int)
            def get_int():
              return '1'
        
            assert get_int() == 1
        
            @anticipate(str)
            def get_str():
              return 22
        
            assert get_str() == '22'
        
            @anticipate([str])
            def get_strs(*args):
              return args
        
            assert list(get_strs(1, 2, 3)) == ['1', '2', '3']
        
        Works much better with your own objects or with `SpringField <https://github.com/six8/springfield>`_
        
        
